OL,5, Anti-poverty campaigners are calling   
OL,6, for housing associations to stop       
OL,7, tearing up carpets between tenants and 
OL,8, leaving many with bare floors.         
OL,10,FMost social landlords rip up flooring  
OL,11,Fwhen a tenant moves out due to hygiene 
OL,12,F- but it's not always replaced quickly.
OL,14,FSome 1.2 million people in the UK have 
OL,15,Fno carpet or flooring in their bedrooms
OL,16,Fand living areas, a survey suggests.   
OL,18,FLena and her son moved into a flat in  
OL,19,FOldham months ago but the floors are   
OL,20,Fstill bare.                            
